article.description: — Ezekiel Alley had a season-high 22 points as Portland State ended its seven-game home losing streak, holding off Northern Colorado to earn a 79-76 win on Monday night.
article.headline: Alley leads Portland St. past N. Colorado 79-76
article.linkText: Alley leads Portland St. past N. Colorado 79-76
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- — Ezekiel Alley had a season-high 22 points as Portland State ended its seven-game home losing streak, holding off Northern Colorado to earn a 79-76 win on Monday night. Damion Squire had 19 points for Portland State (6-13, 4-7 Big Sky Conference). Marlon Ruffin added 12 points. Ian Burke had 11 points. Daylen Kountz had 30 points for the Bears (10-10, 5-3). Matt Johnson II added 17 points. Dru Kuxhausen had 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
